#import "@local/elektroedde:0.1.0": *
#show: problem

=
A charge $q$ sits at the back corner of a cube, as shown in the figure. What is the flux of $vb(E)$ through the shaded side?

#solution[
  Adding 7 cubes to totally enclose the charge gives a total of 24 faces that the flux is passing through. This means that the flux of this one surface is 1/24 of the total flux given by the charge $q$.
  $
    "[Flux through the shaded surface]" = q/(24 epsilon_0)
  $
]